\"to\": 103}, {\"ngram\": \"the others\", \"from\": 115, \"to\": 125}, {\"ngram\": \"our lives\", \"from\": 131, \"to\": 140}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are patronuses warding off the darkness of Britain's sordid riots - showing that to stand proudly beneath a flag can be something pure and vital, and a gesture full of friendship.\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 201, \"end\": 208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.6164371276249567, \"rank\": 0.6222248760381116, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"patronuses\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 172}, {\"ngram\": \"the darkness\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 197}, {\"ngram\": \"a flag\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 270}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 287}, {\"ngram\": \"a gesture\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 317}, {\"ngram\": \"friendship\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 336}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the diversity of sports at these Games - from the waterborne pinball of kayak cross to the perfect ten seconds of the 100metres - it is impossible, my friends, not to find something to love.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 416, \"end\": 421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"score\": 0.9528293581266772, \"rank\": 0.049505865316596696, \"text\": \"kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the diversity\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 357}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 367}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 382}, {\"ngram\": \"the waterborne pinball\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"the perfect ten seconds\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100metres\", \"from\": 458, \"to\": 471}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 525}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And, even better, because this moment is rare - these athletes do not only want to win, they want to tell you why their sport is special and what it all means to them and their own.\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 717, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this moment\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 573}, {\"ngram\": \"these athletes\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"their sport\", \"from\": 650, \"to\": 661}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympians - except in a few obvious cases - are not actually jocks.\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 786, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 728}, {\"ngram\": \"a few obvious cases\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 760}, {\"ngram\": \"jocks\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 785}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What they are is nerds.\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nerds\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 809}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are obsessed with something quite unusual.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 858, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And now they are being celebrated, perhaps only briefly, for having found something unlikely they love to do.\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 942}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the wake ofMondo Duplantis' world-record vaultat a stunned Stade de France, people kept asking: just how do you find out you are good at THAT?\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1115, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wake ofMondo Duplantis' world-record vaultat\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1021}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1055}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his case, he was leaping bars at four - pole vault is a family trade.\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his case\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1127}, {\"ngram\": \"bars\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1148}, {\"ngram\": \"four - pole vault\", \"from\": 1152, \"to\": 1169}, {\"ngram\": \"a family trade\", \"from\": 1173, \"to\": 1187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But so much of it comes down to luck, useful genes, trying hard, getting up again and again, having the right people around you and really, really liking what it is you are doing.\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1369, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \", useful genes\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1240}, {\"ngram\": \"the right people\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not football, the rewards are not weekly and trimmed in gold.\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1439, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"football\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1390}, {\"ngram\": \"the rewards\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1403}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The attention will fade.\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1464, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The attention\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have had the privilege of talking with champions, medallists and would-be medallists for Eurosport nearly non-stop since the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1610, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the privilege\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1490}, {\"ngram\": \"champions\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"medallists\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"would-be medallists\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"Eurosport\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1609}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's where I have seen how much Olympians want to commute what they are doing into something even more important.\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1730, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1709}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After interviewing British kayak cross silver medallist Joe Clarke I made a throwaway remark about how incredible his sport looked from the sidelines and how excited I was to get back to the UK and try it.\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.6841983724622853, \"rank\": 0.4180294907961667, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1788, \"end\": 1791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"score\": 0.8470262414014618, \"rank\": 0.17876866029999136, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\"}, {\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9998954527530437, \"rank\": 9.87730728832126e-05, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a throwaway remark\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1824}, {\"ngram\": \"his sport\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1855}, {\"ngram\": \"the sidelines\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He immediately started helping me make plans - explaining where to go and how easy it is to get started; he wanted me to make a commitment to get on the water.\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 2099, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"plans\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1984}, {\"ngram\": \"a commitment\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2078}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was proud others might love it as he did.\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2144, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"proud others\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2119}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's not all that speaking with Olympians seconds after the greatest moment of their life - or their most crushing disappointment - has shown me.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2294, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2189}, {\"ngram\": \"the greatest moment\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2223}, {\"ngram\": \"their life\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2237}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What's more, what I have learned relates to us all.\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2346, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Firstly, one person's silver medal is not another's.\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2400, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one person's silver medal\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2382}, {\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2397}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When you step up to talk to anyone, you have to know their context, and you have to try to read their emotion.\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2435}, {\"ngram\": \"their context\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2467}, {\"ngram\": \"their emotion\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2510}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's what everyone else wants to share in and empathise with at the Olympics, and it's what TV is so uniquely set up to express.\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2642, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2524, \"to\": 2532}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2578, \"to\": 2590}, {\"ngram\": \"TV\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2608}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Secondly, that everyone wants to share their joy with their family, their friends, their teachers, their dogs (see: T. Pidcock) when they have got the gold.\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2800, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2667}, {\"ngram\": \"their joy\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2692}, {\"ngram\": \"their family\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"their friends\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2725}, {\"ngram\": \"their teachers\", \"from\": 2727, \"to\": 2741}, {\"ngram\": \"their dogs\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2753}, {\"ngram\": \"T. Pidcock\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2770}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold\", \"from\": 2791, \"to\": 2799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But almost always they hit out at themselves when they have missed.\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2869, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Great support will reflect joy at you, and it's something magnified by being shared, but it goes the other way too.\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2985, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Great support\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2883}, {\"ngram\": \"joy\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 2900}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2918, \"to\": 2927}, {\"ngram\": \"the other way\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 2980}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's my fault, I made a mistake,' said rower Ollie Wynne-Griffith, devastated after missing out on men's pair gold despite leading throughout.\", \"from\": 2986, \"to\": 3129, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my fault\", \"from\": 2992, \"to\": 3000}, {\"ngram\": \"a mistake\", \"from\": 3009, \"to\": 3018}, {\"ngram\": \"rower Ollie Wynne-Griffith\", \"from\": 3026, \"to\": 3052}, {\"ngram\": \"men's pair gold\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3101}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like Ollie, we need our people to cushion the self-criticism when life is tough.\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3210, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ollie\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3140}, {\"ngram\": \"our people\", \"from\": 3150, \"to\": 3160}, {\"ngram\": \"the self-criticism\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3190}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, that most people do not 'feel' at the moment of their greatest triumph.\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3292, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"most people\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3237}, {\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3265}, {\"ngram\": \"their greatest triumph\", \"from\": 3269, \"to\": 3291}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They can understand it logically but it's about as real to them as it is to us watching.\", \"from\": 3293, \"to\": 3381, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3369, \"to\": 3371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So when you are speaking to them just afterwards, they are pure emotion.\", \"from\": 3383, \"to\": 3455, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"pure emotion\", \"from\": 3442, \"to\": 3454}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their adrenaline is crashing and they are intoxicated basically, riding waves of what's just happened for the first time.\", \"from\": 3456, \"to\": 3577, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their adrenaline\", \"from\": 3456, \"to\": 3472}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3533}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 3562, \"to\": 3576}]}, {\"sentence\": \"British gold medallist Emily Craig put it the most beautifully of all after she became Olympic champion with her partner Imogen Grant three years after missing out on a rowing medal by 0.1 seconds: 'You are talking to two people who are standing here with everything we have ever wanted in our entire lives and we do not know what to do.'\", \"from\": 3579, \"to\": 3917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3579, \"end\": 3586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.6841983724622853, \"rank\": 0.41802